    "created_at": "2014-07-28T20:11:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-28T20:11:43Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm arguing from a uniformity of user experience point of view - why should some functionality be available when a cell of one type and not another? For example, if I have a notebook where I want to turn the entire thing into one cell - why would you prevent me from merging it all? I have multi-line heading cells (from the perspective of how they appear in the code mirror editor) with HTML inside of them.\n\nThe cell type is orthogonal to the editing done within a cell, so I should be able to split any cell. Same goes for merging, since it is the inverse of split.\n"
  },
